## PABLO-D-108: API Contract & Design Report

### 1. Full API Contract Summary

The contract defines 5 domains with specific implementation priorities:

**Domain A: Auth & User** (existing endpoints, no changes)
- `GET /health` — health/connectivity check
- `GET /api/users/me/status` — check if authenticated
- `GET /api/users/me` — fetch therapist profile for speaker labels
- `GET /api/users/me/baa-status` — check BAA acceptance
- `POST /api/users/me/accept-baa` — accept BAA (onboarding gate)

**Domain B: Patients** (existing endpoints, companion needs UI)
- `GET /api/patients` — paginated list with optional search
- `GET /api/patients/{id}` — single patient detail
- `POST /api/patients` — create new patient
- `PATCH /api/patients/{id}` — update patient fields

**Domain C: Session Scheduling** (NEW — highest priority)
- `POST /api/sessions/schedule` — create scheduled session
- `GET /api/sessions/today` — fetch today's scheduled sessions (with inline patient summary to avoid N+1)
- `PATCH /api/sessions/{id}/status` — transition session status (validates state machine, sets `started_at` / `ended_at`)
- `PATCH /api/sessions/{id}` — update session metadata (reschedule, change video link, etc.)

Session status lifecycle: `scheduled` → `in_progress` → `recording_complete` → `queued` → `processing` → `pending_review` → `finalized` (or `failed`)

New session model fields:
- `scheduled_at` (datetime)
- `video_link` (string, optional)
- `video_platform` (enum: `zoom`, `teams`, `meet`, `none`)
- `session_type` (enum: `individual`, `couples`)
- `duration_minutes` (int, default 50)
- `source` (enum: `web`, `companion`, `calendar`)
- `started_at` / `ended_at` (datetimes, set server-side on transitions)

**Domain D: Transcript Upload** (NEW — second priority)
- `POST /api/sessions/{id}/transcript` — upload transcript, triggers SOAP pipeline

Request body:
```json
{
  "format": "google_meet",
  "content": "Google Meet Transcript\n..."
}
```

Side effects: transitions `recording_complete` → `queued`, kicks off SOAP pipeline.

**Domain E: SOAP Notes & History** (existing endpoints)
- `GET /api/sessions` — browse past sessions with pagination
- `GET /api/sessions/{id}` — session detail with SOAP note
- `PATCH /api/sessions/{id}/finalize` — finalize with quality rating (1-5)

**Domain F: User Preferences** (NEW — lower priority)
- `GET /api/users/me/preferences` — fetch preferences (or defaults)
- `PUT /api/users/me/preferences` — save preferences (full replace)

Fields: `default_video_platform`, `default_session_type`, `default_duration_minutes`, `auto_transcribe`, `quality_preset`, `therapist_display_name`

**Global conventions:**
- Base URL configured per-environment via `GET /api/config` from auth server
- All `/api/*` endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer <firebase_id_token>` (except `/health`)
- All requests include `X-Client-Type: pablo-companion-macos/1.0` header
- All JSON uses `snake_case` keys; Swift decoder uses `.convertFromSnakeCase`
- Consistent error format: `{ "detail": "...", "error_code": "...", "field": "..." }` with HTTP 400/401/403/404/409/500

